ve an established reputation for dedication to their clients and aggressive legal counsel. If you have been injured by a defective product in Dallas, Arlington, Plano, or anywhere in Texas, contact us today to find out if you have a viable defective product claim and to get started on the path towards getting appropriate compensation. Call our Dallas office at 214-504-2121 or call toll free at 855-584-8787.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-12 08:49:00', '2013-09-12 08:49:00', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('221', '1', '2013-09-12 08:58:11', '2013-09-12 08:58:11', '<h1>When You Have a Defective Product Claim, You Need the Experience of Dallas Personal Injury Attorneys</h1>\r\n\r\nThousands of Americans are injured by defective products each year. These products can include toys, appliances, electrical wiring, power tools, loading and construction equipment, and flammable materials. There are three different types of product liability\r\n<ul class=\"yes\">\r\n   <li> Defectively manufactured products</li>\r\n    <li> Defectively designed products</li>\r\n    <li> Products with insufficient warnings or instructions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere is no one law governing defective products in the U.S.; instead, product liability cases in Texas are considered in light of state negligence, breach of warranty, and strict liability laws. Any number of companies or individuals could be found guilty in a defective product suit, including the manufacturer, the person who constructed or installed the product, wholesale distributors, and retailers â anyone who helped to distribute the product and had sufficient reason to believe it was unsafe. Because of the complexity of product liability laws and the difficulty in proving exactly who was responsible, defective product cases require personal injury attorneys with years of experience in this legal sphere. At Powers Taylor, we have the experience necessary to aggressively defend your case.\r\n\r\nContact Powers Taylor to Get the Financial Compensation You Deserve\r\n\r\nDefective products can cause serious injuries that result in high medical bills, pain and suffering, and time off from work. When you have been injured because of manufacturer or retailer negligence, justice demands that you should not have to pay for your injuries. At Powers Taylor, we are committed to serving justice and to ensuring that you get full financial compensation for all losses you have sustained. Our Dallas-Fort Worth attorneys and litigators have an established reputation for dedication to their clients and aggressive legal counsel. If you have been injured by a defective product in Dallas, Arlington, Plano, or anywhere in Texas, contact us today to find out if you have a viable defective product claim and to get started on the path towards getting appropriate compensation. Call our Dallas office at 214-504-2121 or call toll free at 855-584-8787.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-12 08:58:11', '2013-09-12 08:58:11', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
