on to their clients and aggressive legal counsel. If you have been injured by a defective product in Dallas, Arlington, Plano, or anywhere in Texas, contact us today to find out if you have a viable defective product claim and to get started on the path towards getting appropriate compensation. Call our Dallas office at 214-504-2121 or call toll free at 855-584-8787.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-19 12:25:25', '2013-09-19 12:25:25', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('230', '1', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '<h1>Criminal Defense Attorney in Connecticut</h1>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\nAttorney Jonathan R. Sills is a partner in the criminal defense law firm of TOMEO SILLS, LLC. and he has a statewide practice for representing clients in criminal and DUI matters. He handles criminal matters in every Geographical Area (G.A.) Court in Connecticut as well as the Judicial District (J.D.) Courts throughout the State.\r\n\r\nAttorney Sills was recently promoted to Senior partner by the firmâs founder, Steven A. Tomeo and together the two (2) partners author the Connecticut Practice Book Series book CONNECTICUT DUI LAW, which is published by West Publishing Company.\r\n\r\nAttorney Sills represents individuals at the Department of Motor Vehicles. The main office is located at 60 State Street, Wethersfield, CT 06161. DMV Hearings are also located at DMV offices located in Bridgeport, Old Saybrook and Waterbury. The firm has offices near each DMV location.\r\n\r\nAttorney Sills is no stranger to the Appellate Court process in the Connecticut Appellate Court in Hartford and the filing of Administrative Appeals to the Superior Court, New Britain Judicial District in New Britain.\r\n\r\nTHE FIRMâS TOLL FREE LINE IS 800-608-6636 FOR ALL OFFICES.\r\n\r\nThe convenience of each location enables the client to meet with the attorney at a location nearest the client. If you have a matter pending at one of the following courts, please call one of the above listed offices for a FREE CONSULTATION.\r\n\r\nThe Criminal Division hears cases where the state is prosecuting a person (the defendant) who is accused of breaking the law. The state is represented by a stateâs attorney. There are three kinds of criminal cases, depending on the severity of the offense: crimes which include felonies â punishable by prison sentences more than one year â and misdemeanors â punishable by prison sentences of one year or less; violations which include motor vehicle cases punishable by a fine only; and, infractions where a fine may be paid by mail without requiring a court appearance (for example, traffic tickets). All criminal cases but the most serious ones are heard in geographical area courts around the state.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('241', '1', '2013-09-24 12:26:19', '2013-09-24 12:26:19', '<h1>Helping You Regain Control of Your Financial Future</h1>\r\n<hr>\r\nWhen there is not enough money to cover all your bills, it is easy to feel overwhelmed. If you are in debt, you may be pressured by creditors to pay money you do not have. It can get to the point at which you fear picking up the phone or going through your mail. Financial distress can also make it difficult to concentrate at work, as well as cause you to avoid social situations. Fortunately, you have the power to get back on track with your finances.\r\n\r\nAt  Andrew L. Campbell Attorney At Law, we work with people and small businesses to find debt relief and mortgage solutions that give them financial breathing room to make a fresh start. Through bankruptcy, loan modification and other alternatives, we can help you stop foreclosure, repossession and garnishment. There is a reason we are known as the \"home savers\" in Flint, Michigan.\r\n\r\nTo discuss your debt relief options during a free consultation, please call. Our firm has helped thousands of people step out of the darkness into the light. We can help you.\r\n\r\nAndrew L. Campbell Attorney At Law Advantage\r\n\r\nOur founding attorney set out to build a responsive, client-centered law firm committed to helping individuals and small business owners find debt relief. We concentrate exclusively on turning financial chaos into a solid foundation, ready for the rebuilding of a stable financial future.\r\n\r\nWe are proud to offer large firm experience with small firm service. We understand that people get into debt for a number of reasons. In a casual and accepting environment, we will listen to your situation without judgment. We recognize that our clients are in the midst of a challenging time and strive to reduce the stress by giving them the necessary information to make an informed decision about debt relief.\r\n\r\nBy focusing on your financial circumstances, we can offer real solutions, such as bankruptcy and bankruptcy alternatives, including mortgage loan modifications and personal and small business reorganizations. Because the last thing you need to worry about when you are in debt is how to pay your lawyer, our office offers long-term payment plans. ', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-24 12:26:19', '2013-09-24 12:26:19', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
