es, we can offer real solutions, such as bankruptcy and bankruptcy alternatives, including mortgage loan modifications and personal and small business reorganizations. Because the last thing you need to worry about when you are in debt is how to pay your lawyer, our office offers long-term payment plans. ', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-24 12:26:40', '2013-09-24 12:26:40', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('248', '1', '2013-09-30 11:42:03', '2013-09-30 11:42:03', '<h1>Focusing on Criminal-Related Offenses</h1>\r\nFacing a criminal charge is ALWAYS a serious matter requiring serious defense. Our criminal defense practice takes every case seriously. As an experienced Criminal Defense Team, we know that even a misdemeanor can have a devastating effect upon your life. In our practice, there is no such thing as a simple criminal matter.\r\n\r\nFrom DUI and Drug Charges to Vehicular Homicide, Invountary Manslaughter and Premeditated Murder, in Municipal, State or Federal Court, we provide defense of all criminal matters. Contact our office today for a free consultation to discuss the facts and circumstances of your case and to determine the best strategy for a strong defense.\r\n\r\nWhen you are charged with a crime, it is not the time to pick a lawyer at random.  You need a lawyer who has experience, practices exclusively in criminal defense, is known and respected in the jurisdiction where your case is charged, and is devoted to getting the very best result possible in your case.\r\n\r\nSuccess in each case can be measured in different ways. The âgold standardâ in criminal defense is outright acquittal of the charges at trial, or dismissal of the charges due to inadmissibility of evidence. Success in a manslaughter case or federal charges with damaging evidence may require extensive negotiations with the prosecutor for conviction on a lesser charge or a recommendation of probation as opposed to imprisonment. No matter what criminal charges you face, your defense should be thoroughly researched, meticulously planned and aggressively litigated. One of my criminal defense strategies is a simple one â We strive to work harder than the prosecution.\r\n\r\nIf you are facing criminal charges, do not leave the outcome of the case or your future to chance. Secure the representation, advice, and counsel of a qualified attorney with experience defending people against criminal charges.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-30 11:42:03', '2013-09-30 11:42:03', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('255', '1', '2013-10-08 06:02:50', '2013-10-08 06:02:50', '<h1>New York Civil Trial Litigation Attorney</h1>\r\nI am a trial lawyer based in Long Island, New York with a highly personalized practice in both State and Federal Courts here in New York and other states.\r\n\r\nMy practice consists of diverse civil litigation with a concentration in representing plaintiffs who have been monetarily, physically or reputationally injured. This office handles a wide variety of civil litigation ranging from business disputes and securities fraud to libel, sexual harassment and medical malpractice.\r\n \r\nThis office combines the personalized attention to your case that is only available in a boutique law firm, with the resources of large firms. By partnering with large firms for larger cases, and establishing working relationships favorable to my clients, I have delivered small firm personalized attention with large firm manpower and support resources.\r\n\r\nThe challenge of winning motions and trials often depends upon the lawyer\'s ability to simplify the complex and strike a resonant theme. At its core litigating a case consists of communicating a story. To the victim of wrongful treatment it is perhaps the most important story they have to tell. I consider it a gift to have a vocation which enables me to provide such a service.\r\n\r\nEdward Miller is a civil trial attorney with thirty years of experience in cases ranging from libel and slander to securities class actions. In the late 90\'s, Mr.Miller led a trial team of four different law firms in the consolidated cases Webb vs. United Automobile Workers in central Illinois, and in 2005 through 2008 Miller led a trial team in a series of lawsuits against the New York State Department of Corrections.\r\n\r\nHaving appeared on ABC World News Tonight and Court T.V.in connection with high profile cases, Miller has won all but two of the over twenty jury trials he has taken to verdict.\r\n\r\nAt the conclusion of his first jury trial, Cuyahoga County Court of Common Pleas Judge R. Donahue wrote of Miller:\r\n\r\n    âParticularly in light of the clear and unarguable nature of the uniqueness of this case Mr. Miller has demonstrated skill, attention and ability in achieving the final jury result.â\r\n', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-08 06:02:50', '2013-10-08 06:02:50', '', '29', 'http://localhost/odelugojohnsonlaw/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
